laboratory_examinations.findings: Unable to rule out pathogens due to overgrowth of swarming Proteus spp.

Lung volumes remain low. Heart is at upper limits of normal in size. Mild pulmonary vascular congestion persists, probable mild interstitial edema. Improving bibasilar atelectasis, more pronounced on the right than left, and probable very small pleural effusions. Upper lobe predominant emphysema noted.
